Token.Abstract: The MBEnvironment class contains the state of the Mockingbird Data Environment.
Retrieves the MBEnvironment instance representing the currently-active environment.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The currently-active environment.

Token.Abstract: Sets the active MBEnvironment instance. The active environment supplies the MBVariableSpace instance used to evaluate expressions by default.

Parameter.Name: env
Parameter.Abstract: The MBEnvironment to set as the active environment.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The previously-active MBEnvironment instance, if any.

Token.Abstract: Sets the active MBEnvironment instance by pushing a new environment onto the environment stack.

Parameter.Name: env
Parameter.Abstract: The MBEnvironment to set as the active environment.

Token.Abstract: Sets the active MBEnvironment instance by popping it from the environment stack.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-active environment.

Token.Abstract: Returns (but does not remove) the MBEnvironment instance at the top of the environment stack. This is the environment that would become active if popEnvironment were called.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The environment at the top of the environment stack, or nil if there is nothing in the stack.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new default environment, bypassing any manifest.xml file that might exist in the application's resources. The default environment is the environment that exists before any manifest file is processed.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest.xml file found in the application's resources.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest.xml file found in the specified search directory or in the application's resources.

Parameter.Name: dirPath
Parameter.Abstract: The path of a directory that will be searched when trying to locate the manifest and other MBML files. This directory will be the first one searched when MBML files are referenced. If a given file doesn't exist in dirPath, the resourceSearchBundles will then be searched.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest file with the given name found in the application's resources.

Parameter.Name: manifestName
Parameter.Abstract: The name of the manifest file.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest file with the given name found in the specified search directory or in the application's resources.

Parameter.Name: manifestName
Parameter.Abstract: The name of the manifest file.

Parameter.Name: dirPath
Parameter.Abstract: The path of a directory that will be searched when trying to locate the manifest and other MBML files. This directory will be the first one searched when MBML files are referenced. If a given file doesn't exist in dirPath, the resourceSearchBundles will then be searched.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest.xml file found in the specified search directories or in the application's resources.

Parameter.Name: dirPaths
Parameter.Abstract: An array containing the paths of directories that will be searched when trying to locate the manifest and other MBML files. These directories will be searched first (and in the order specified by dirPaths) when MBML files are referenced. If a given file can't be found in the any of the directories specified by dirPaths, the resourceSearchBundles will then be searched.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Loads a new environment by processing the manifest file with the given name found in the specified search directories or in the application's resources.

Parameter.Name: manifestName
Parameter.Abstract: The name of the manifest file.

Parameter.Name: dirPaths
Parameter.Abstract: An array containing the paths of directories that will be searched when trying to locate the manifest and other MBML files. These directories will be searched first (and in the order specified by dirPaths) when MBML files are referenced. If a given file can't be found in the any of the directories specified by dirPaths, the resourceSearchBundles will then be searched.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The newly-loaded, now-active MBEnvironment instance, or nil if the environment could not be loaded.

Token.Abstract: Attempts to load the specified MBML file.

Parameter.Name: fileName
Parameter.Abstract: The name of the MBML file to load. Note that this is not a path name. MBML file loading follows a specific search order that allows files to reference each other by name without knowing precisely where they're located.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if fileName was loaded successfully; NO otherwise.

Token.Abstract: Adds the specified bundle as one that will be consulted whenever an environment attempts to find a resource such as an MBML file.

Parameter.Name: bundle
Parameter.Abstract: An NSBundle instance that should be searched when attempting to find resources.

Token.Abstract: Returns the NSBundle instances that will be consulted whenever an environment attempts to find a resource such as an MBML file.

ReturnValue.Abstract: An array of NSBundles. Will never be nil.

Token.Abstract: Returns YES if the environment is loaded; NO otherwise.

If the environment was loaded using a manifest file, this property will return the path of the manifest file. If the environment isn't loaded or if the environment was loaded without using a manifest file (such as through the loadDefaultEnvironment method), this value will be nil.

Determines if an MBML file with a specific path has been loaded by the receiver.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the environment has loaded an MBML file at the path filePath; NO otherwise.

Token.Abstract: Determines if an MBML file with a specific name has been loaded by the receiver.

Parameter.Name: fileName
Parameter.Abstract: The filename, also known as the last path component.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the environment has loaded an MBML file with the given name; NO otherwise.

Token.Abstract: Allows the loading of environment classes from libraries whose class names begin with the specified prefix.

Parameter.Name: prefix
Parameter.Abstract: The class prefix Mockingbird should support for dynamic class loading.

Token.Abstract: Returns an array containing the class prefixes that will be searched when attempting to load environment classes.

ReturnValue.Abstract: An array of strings containing the supported class prefixes. Will never be nil and will always contain at least one value, the string "MB".

Token.Abstract: Uses the supportedClassPrefixes to find an available Class that implements the class with the specified name.

Parameter.Name: className
Parameter.Abstract: The class name for which a Class is sought.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A Class for className, if a class exists among the supported class prefixes, or without any prefix. Returns nil if no class could be found.

Token.Abstract: Enables the MBModule represented by the specified class. When new MBEnvironment instances are created, they will gain support for the features added by the module implementation.

Parameter.Name: cls
Parameter.Abstract: The implementing class of the MBModule to enable.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if cls represents an MBModule that is now enabled. Will be NO if cls does not conform to MBModule.

Token.Abstract: Returns an array containing the MBModule classes that will be enabled for all newly-created environments. Note when a given environment instance is loaded, additional modules not included in this array may be enabled through the manifest file.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The currently-enabled modules. Will always contain at least one item, because MBDataEnvironmentModule is always enabled.

Token.Abstract: Returns an array of Classes representing the MBModules enabled in the receiver.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The modules enabled in the receiving environment. Will always contain at least one item, because MBDataEnvironmentModule is always enabled. Additional modules may also be enabled through the manifest file.

Token.Abstract: Returns an array of MBEnvironmentLoader instances representing the environment loaders consulted when the receiving environment is loaded.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The environment loaders used by the receiver. Will never be nil.

Token.Abstract: Returns the first MBEnvironmentLoader instance known to the receiver that is an instance of the given class.

Parameter.Name: cls
Parameter.Abstract: The class for which an implementing MBEnvironmentLoader instance is sought.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The first MBEnvironmentLoader representing an instance of cls. Will be nil if no such environment loader was found.
